Metathorax
: dorsally with 2 pairs of short setae as on each abdominal segment. Ventral part of metapleural ridge (plr 
3
) short but well-sclerotised; without either a metepisternum (eps 
3
) or a precoxal ridge (pcr 
3
); metepimeron (epm 
3
) absent. Metathoracic spiracles (sp 
3
) small, width of peritreme about 13 µm, each with an associated lp. Metasternum (stn 
3
) unsclerotised, with few setae; metasternal apophyses well developed.
